{"word":"γανόω","slug":"γανόω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>γανόω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>from <el>γάνος</el>\n<p/><i>to make bright</i>:— <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be made glad, exult</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>; <a href='S:participle'>part.</a> <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <el>γεγανωμένος</el>, like <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>nitidus, glad-looking, joyous</el>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/>"}]}